     1	# Backend Provenance Map
     2	
     3	## Scope
     4	
     5	- Pass: `backend-provenance-pass`
     6	- Mode: local code and migration evidence only (no live execution in this pass)
     7	- Coverage focus: migration lineage, seed lineage, queue -> execution -> projection publication, replay/restore paths, authoritative vs derived table families
     8	
     9	## Primary Evidence
    10	
    11	- Migration runner and ordering: `air-mentor-api/src/db/migrate.ts`
    12	- Seed orchestration: `air-mentor-api/src/db/seed.ts`, `air-mentor-api/src/lib/msruas-proof-sandbox.ts`
    13	- Queue claim/lease/heartbeat/failure: `air-mentor-api/src/lib/proof-run-queue.ts`
    14	- Main proof control plane: `air-mentor-api/src/lib/msruas-proof-control-plane.ts`
    15	- Seeded run finalization: `air-mentor-api/src/lib/proof-control-plane-seeded-run-service.ts`
    16	- Runtime replay/recompute: `air-mentor-api/src/lib/proof-control-plane-runtime-service.ts`
    17	- Semester activation bridge: `air-mentor-api/src/lib/proof-control-plane-activation-service.ts`
    18	- Checkpoint/queue summary semantics: `air-mentor-api/src/lib/proof-control-plane-checkpoint-service.ts`
    19	- Migrations 0000..0018 in `air-mentor-api/src/db/migrations/`
    20	
    21	## Migration Lineage Delta (0009-0018)
    22	
    23	- `0009_student_agent_shell.sql`: adds student-agent card/session/message persistence keyed by `simulation_run_id`, `student_id`, and optional viewer context.
    24	- `0010_simulation_stage_playback.sql`: introduces checkpointed stage playback families (`simulation_stage_checkpoints`, student/offering/queue projections) and binds agent cards/sessions to checkpoint IDs.
    25	- `0011_risk_model_artifacts.sql`: formalizes risk evidence snapshots and risk model artifact registry (versioned JSON payload/evaluation).
    26	- `0012_*`: adds queue-case governance (`simulation_stage_queue_cases`), assignment enrichment (`assigned_faculty_id`), reassessment resolution payload extension, and faculty calendar admin workspace state.
    27	- `0013_scope_governance_profiles_and_provisioning.sql`: introduces policy/profile override surfaces and profile fingerprint propagation into runs/artifacts; adds `offering_stage_advancement_audits` and finals lock bit.
    28	- `0014_async_proof_run_queue.sql`: adds async run progress and worker lease fields on `simulation_runs` plus queue/lease indexes.
    29	- `0015_curriculum_linkage_candidates.sql`: introduces linkage-candidate review table for curriculum graph candidate edges.
    30	- `0016_login_rate_limit_windows.sql`: adds auth protection window table.
    31	- `0017_operational_telemetry_events.sql`: adds operational telemetry event sink with timestamp/level indexes.
    32	- `0018_proof_active_operational_semester.sql`: adds and backfills `simulation_runs.active_operational_semester`.
    33	
    34	## Seed Provenance
    35	
    36	- `seedDatabase()` runs SQL migrations first, then platform data seeding, then proof sandbox seeding.
    37	- Platform seed source-of-truth is `air-mentor-api/src/db/seeds/platform.seed.json` applied through `seedIntoDatabase(...)`.
    38	- Proof synthetic corpus is layered by `seedMsruasProofSandbox(...)` and downstream proof-control-plane run generation.
    39	- Consequence: provenance has two root seeds: platform baseline + synthetic proof runtime corpus.
    40	
    41	## Queue -> Run -> Projection Completion Chain
    42	
    43	1. Enqueue/retry writes queue-ready run rows (status/progress/policy snapshot) on `simulation_runs`.
    44	2. Worker (`startProofRunWorker`) polls and claims next run with lease token and lease expiry.
    45	3. Worker heartbeats lease; execution delegates to `startProofSimulationRun(...)`.
    46	4. Seeded finalization writes bulk runtime families and marks run `completed` (+metrics/progress).
    47	5. Activation path marks target run `active`, deactivates peers in same batch, and calls `publishOperationalProjection(...)`.
    48	6. Projection publication rewrites/refreshes transcript, attendance, assessment, risk, alert, elective operational tables for active scope.
    49	
    50	## Restore and Replay Paths
    51	
    52	- Snapshot restore: `restoreProofSimulationSnapshot(...)` loads latest (or requested) reset snapshot and launches a new run with `parentSimulationRunId`, typically activated.
    53	- Stage playback rebuild: seeded finalize and runtime recompute both invoke `rebuildSimulationStagePlayback(...)` to regenerate checkpoint projections.
    54	- Risk artifact rebuild: seeded finalize and runtime recompute can invoke `rebuildProofRiskArtifacts(...)` to refresh artifact family.
    55	- Active-only risk recompute: `recomputeObservedOnlyRisk(...)` clears active derived rows, rebuilds evidence/risk/alert/reassessment with current observed state and active artifacts.
    56	- Semester activation replay bridge: `activateProofOperationalSemester(...)` updates `simulation_runs.active_operational_semester` and `batches.current_semester`; if run is active, republishes operational projection.
    57	
    58	## Authoritative vs Derived Record Families
    59	
    60	- Identity/auth/session authoritative: login/session/rate-limit windows (`login_rate_limit_windows`) and role grants.
    61	- Academic runtime authoritative: observed semester states, assessments, attendance, interventions, ownership/allocations.
    62	- Proof run control authoritative: `simulation_runs` (+lease/progress), reset snapshots, stage checkpoints, queue cases.
    63	- Derived projection families: stage student/offering/queue projections; operational projection rewrites for transcript/attendance/assessment/risk/alert/elective views.
    64	- Risk evidence/artifact families: `risk_evidence_snapshots` (row-level provenance payload), `risk_model_artifacts` (versioned model/correlation bundles), `risk_assessments`/alerts/reassessment derived from those inputs.
    65	- Governance/provisioning families: policy overrides, curriculum feature profiles/bindings/overrides, stage advancement audits.
    66	
    67	## Drift and Integrity Risks
    68	
    69	- Migration numbering reuse (`0002_*`, `0012_*`) is execution-safe because full filename sort is deterministic, but human review can misread temporal intent.
    70	- Projection publication intentionally performs delete-and-rebuild patterns for proof scope; partial failures could transiently expose stale or sparse projections if transaction boundaries are not end-to-end.
    71	- Active recompute can emit fallback provenance (`coEvidenceMode: fallback-simulated`) when stage evidence is unavailable; consumers must not treat fallback rows as full-fidelity stage evidence.
    72	- Run activation sets all same-batch runs to `completed` before re-activating one target run; external tooling that assumes single-row mutation may misinterpret this as unexpected mass status normalization.
    73	
    74	## Open Questions / Uncovered Scope
    75	
    76	- Need full endpoint-to-table consumer map for each derived family (especially admin proof dashboard and cross-role read surfaces).
    77	- Need live verification for queue worker timing and projection publication atomicity under deployed conditions.
    78	- Need explicit transaction/rollback guarantees review for large delete+insert projection writes.
    79	
    80	## Pass Reporting Snapshot
    81	
    82	- Scope covered: backend migration lineage through `0018`, seed provenance, queue worker chain, activation/replay paths, major table family provenance.
    83	- Files updated in this pass: backend provenance map plus final maps/coverage/memory updates listed in pass outputs.
    84	- Uncovered scope remaining: endpoint consumer parity + live execution verification + transactional robustness proof.
    85	- Contradictions found in this pass: none newly added.
    86	- Risks discovered: migration prefix readability risk, projection rewrite transient risk, fallback provenance interpretation risk.
    87	- Routing/provider/account changes: none during this pass segment.
    88	- Caveman usage: none.
    89	- Live verification performed: no.
    90	- Next pass recommendation: `same-student-cross-surface-parity-pass` then credentialed `live-behavior-pass` rerun.
    91	- Manual checkpoint required: yes, before declaring backend provenance fully closed.

