     1	# Proof Refresh Completion Lineage
     2	
     3	## Scope
     4	
     5	- Pass: `proof-refresh-completion-pass`
     6	- Goal: map post-enqueue completion ownership deterministically
     7	- Evidence mode: local code and test artifacts (no live worker observation in this pass)
     8	
     9	## Core Answer (Ownership)
    10	
    11	- Owner of completion after queue insert is the backend in-process proof worker started by Fastify app bootstrap: `startProofRunWorker(...)` from `air-mentor-api/src/lib/proof-run-queue.ts`, wired in `air-mentor-api/src/app.ts`.
    12	- The worker claims queued runs via DB lease, executes `startProofSimulationRun(...)`, and finalizes success/failure state on `simulation_runs`.
    13	- For queued runs not yet materialized, a manual activation fallback can complete execution synchronously in request path through `activateProofSimulationRun(...)` -> `startProofSimulationRun(...)`.
    14	
    15	## End-to-End Trace
    16	
    17	### 1) UI/API refresh trigger
    18	
    19	- Sysadmin frontend calls `apiClient.createProofRun(batchId, ...)` when forcing refresh/retry (`src/system-admin-live-app.tsx`, `src/api/client.ts`).
    20	- API route receives this at `POST /api/admin/batches/:batchId/proof-runs` and enqueues using `enqueueProofSimulationRun(...)` (`air-mentor-api/src/modules/admin-proof-sandbox.ts`).
    21	- Curriculum mutation flows also enqueue through `enqueueProofRefreshForBatches(...)` (`air-mentor-api/src/modules/admin-structure.ts`, `air-mentor-api/src/modules/academic-admin-offerings-routes.ts`).
    22	
    23	### 2) Queue insert / enqueue path
    24	
    25	- `enqueueProofSimulationRun(...)` inserts `simulation_runs` with:
    26	  - `status='queued'`
    27	  - `progress_json={ phase:'queued', percent:0, requestedActivate, mode }`
    28	  - lease fields null (`worker_lease_token`, `worker_lease_expires_at`)
    29	  - run metadata and policy snapshot
    30	- Queue schema support is from migration `0014_async_proof_run_queue.sql` (progress + lease fields, queue/lease indexes).
    31	
    32	### 3) Worker claim / lease / heartbeat
    33	
    34	- Worker bootstrap: `air-mentor-api/src/app.ts` line path where app starts `startProofRunWorker({ db, pool, clock })`.
    35	- Claim loop:
    36	  - poll interval default 5s, lease duration 60s, heartbeat 15s (`proof-run-queue.ts`).
    37	  - SQL claim picks oldest `queued` or lease-expired `running` row (`FOR UPDATE SKIP LOCKED`) and flips to:
    38	    - `status='running'`
    39	    - `worker_lease_token=<leaseToken>`
    40	    - `worker_lease_expires_at=now+lease`
    41	    - `started_at=COALESCE(started_at, now)`
    42	- Heartbeat extends lease expiry while job runs.
    43	
    44	### 4) Completion / failure / retry / abandonment semantics
    45	
    46	- Success path:
    47	  - worker calls `startProofSimulationRun(...)`.
    48	  - then `finalizeProofRunLease(...)` clears lease token/expiry.
    49	  - run terminal success is set by run services (`status='completed'`, `completedAt`, `progressJson.phase='completed'`) in:
    50	    - `air-mentor-api/src/lib/proof-control-plane-seeded-run-service.ts`
    51	    - `air-mentor-api/src/lib/proof-control-plane-live-run-service.ts`
    52	- Failure path:
    53	  - worker calls `failProofRun(...)`:
    54	    - `status='failed'`
    55	    - `failure_code='PROOF_RUN_EXECUTION_FAILED'`
    56	    - `failure_message=<error>`
    57	    - terminal progress payload
    58	    - lease fields cleared
    59	- Retry path:
    60	  - `retryQueuedProofSimulationRun(...)` resets to queued and clears failure/lease fields.
    61	- Abandonment / delayed worker path:
    62	  - lease-expired `running` rows are reclaimable by next worker tick.
    63	  - if no worker process runs, rows remain queued/running until worker returns.
    64	
    65	### 5) Projection publish / downstream consumption
    66	
    67	- `startProofSimulationRun(...)` delegates to seeded/live services, both rebuild stage playback (`rebuildSimulationStagePlayback(...)`) and recompute observed risk.
    68	- Activation path (`activateProofSimulationRun(...)`) sets one run active and calls `publishOperationalProjection(...)`, which rewrites projection-facing tables (attendance/assessment/transcript/risk/alerts/electives for proof scope).
    69	- Dashboard/read-side consumption:
    70	  - backend dashboard aggregator reads run status/progress/worker lease diagnostics (`air-mentor-api/src/lib/proof-control-plane-batch-service.ts`, dashboard diagnostics helper)
    71	  - frontend reads proof dashboard via `getProofDashboard(...)` in `src/api/client.ts`, surfaced in `src/system-admin-live-app.tsx`.
    72	
    73	## Tables / records touched
    74	
    75	- Primary control row: `simulation_runs` (`status`, `progress_json`, `started_at`, `completed_at`, `failure_code`, `failure_message`, `worker_lease_token`, `worker_lease_expires_at`, `active_flag`).
    76	- Completion materialization families (non-exhaustive, key proof projection outputs):
    77	  - `simulation_stage_checkpoints`
    78	  - `simulation_stage_student_projections`
    79	  - `simulation_stage_offering_projections`
    80	  - `simulation_stage_queue_projections`
    81	  - `risk_assessments`
    82	  - `reassessment_events`
    83	  - `alert_decisions`
    84	  - `risk_evidence_snapshots`
    85	  - operational projection targets: `student_attendance_snapshots`, `student_assessment_scores`, `transcript_term_results`, `transcript_subject_results`, `elective_recommendations`
    86	
    87	## Terminal states and proofs
    88	
    89	- Queue-control statuses in codepaths: `queued`, `running`, `failed`, `completed`, `active`, `archived`.
    90	- Proof of worker ownership:
    91	  - app bootstrap starts worker (`app.ts`)
    92	  - worker claim/lease SQL in `proof-run-queue.ts`
    93	  - worker emits `proof.run.claimed`, `proof.run.executed`, `proof.run.failed` telemetry events
    94	- Proof of run terminalization:
    95	  - seeded/live run services set `status='completed'`, `completedAt`, `progressJson.phase='completed'`.
    96	
    97	## Drift risks if worker absent or delayed
    98	
    99	- No out-of-process cron/queue consumer was found in this repository; completion depends on app process running worker loop.
   100	- If worker is down:
   101	  - refresh requests can accumulate in `queued` state.
   102	  - UI may report "queued" without semantic completion.
   103	- If worker dies mid-run:
   104	  - row can be reclaimed only after lease expiry.
   105	  - recovery latency is bounded by lease duration + poll cadence once worker returns.
   106	- Manual mitigation exists but is operator-driven:
   107	  - activating a queued run can force synchronous execution for non-materialized runs via activation endpoint logic.
   108	
   109	## Evidence Paths
   110	
   111	- `air-mentor-api/src/app.ts`
   112	- `air-mentor-api/src/lib/proof-run-queue.ts`
   113	- `air-mentor-api/src/lib/msruas-proof-control-plane.ts`
   114	- `air-mentor-api/src/lib/proof-control-plane-seeded-run-service.ts`
   115	- `air-mentor-api/src/lib/proof-control-plane-live-run-service.ts`
   116	- `air-mentor-api/src/lib/proof-control-plane-runtime-service.ts`
   117	- `air-mentor-api/src/lib/proof-control-plane-batch-service.ts`
   118	- `air-mentor-api/src/modules/admin-proof-sandbox.ts`
   119	- `air-mentor-api/src/modules/admin-structure.ts`
   120	- `air-mentor-api/src/modules/academic-admin-offerings-routes.ts`
   121	- `air-mentor-api/src/db/migrations/0014_async_proof_run_queue.sql`
   122	- `air-mentor-api/src/db/schema.ts`
   123	- `air-mentor-api/tests/proof-run-queue.test.ts`
   124	
   125	## Completion Gate Verdict
   126	
   127	- Gate question: "Who finishes refresh, how, and what proves it?"
   128	- Verdict: **locally satisfied**.
   129	  - Who: in-process backend proof worker (or activation-path synchronous fallback).
   130	  - How: leased queue claim -> proof run execution -> run service completion -> optional activation projection publish.
   131	  - Proof: explicit bootstrap wiring, lease SQL, terminal status writes, and dashboard consumption paths.
   132	- Remaining closure risk: deployed worker liveness and end-to-end live completion still need credentialed runtime verification.

